JOS – Plateau state Commissioners have raised more than N60 million to purchase forms for Governor Simon Bako Lalong, to contest for the Plateau South Senatorial Primaries of All Progressives Congress in Plateau state. This move is led by Yakubu Dati, the chairman of the Commissioner’s Forum of Plateau State. According to Dati in a statement, Governor Simon Lalong has restored Plateau to its place of reckoning by promoting peaceful coexistence and developmental projects for the benefit of the common citizens irrespective of tribe, religion and creed. The Commissioners further enumerated the leadership qualities of Governor Simon Lalong who, as the Chairman of Northern Governors Forum has promoted unity and accommodation amongst different spheres. According to Dati, the senate position will enable the entire country to benefit from Lalong’s demonstrated leadership potential. They encouraged the youths, women, elders, both appointed and elected beneficiaries to join other stakeholders who are meeting day and night to key into the victory train. Joined in this crusade for Lalong to run for Plateau South Senatorial bid are Secretary to the state government Professor Danladi Atu and Chief of staff to Governor Lalong Engr Noel Donjur.